=== Salivary Metabolomic Fingerprint of Sleep Deprivation as Candidate ME/CFS Biomarker
<sec:saliva-sleep-metabolomics>

The absence of a biochemical test for sleep deprivation has been a long-standing gap in both forensic and clinical medicine. Acute sleep loss produces cognitive and motor impairment comparable to alcohol intoxication, yet no objective roadside or clinical assay exists to quantify it. Scholz et al. (2026) demonstrated the first direct salivary metabolomic biomarkers of acute sleep deprivation, achieving 94% classification accuracy with a 12-feature machine learning model @Scholz2026SleepMetabolome.


